  "title": "SALES SPECIALIST TELECOMMUNICATION",
  "description": "<p>- Achieve set sales targets and objectives.</p><p>- Conduct cold calling, prospecting, and lead qualification.</p><p>- Identify new business opportunities and build lasting client relationships.</p><p>- Provide tailored solutions based on client needs to ensure satisfaction.</p><p>- Develop and implement effective sales strategies while monitoring market trends.</p><p>- Collaborate with the team to drive long-term growth and profitability.</p><p>- Build and maintain a strong industry network to stay ahead of competitors.</p><p>- Perform other ad-hoc duties as assigned by the superior<br /></p><p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u><br /></p><p>- Minimum qualification: Secondary N-level or equivalent.</p><p>- Strong interest and ability in sales, with excellent communication skills.</p><p>- Positive, confident, and determined mindset with resilience against rejection.</p><p>- Able to work independently and as part of a team.</p><p>- Target-driven and able to thrive under pressure.</p><p>- Training will be provided.</p><p>- Open to Singaporeans and Work Permit holders.<br /></p><p><u><strong>Compensation</strong></u><br /></p><p>Monthly basic salary: SGD $1,800 to $2,000.</p><p>It provides you with a stable source of income.<br /></p><p>Commission for Business: $50 up to No Cap (Average $250-$2000).</p><p>An attractive performance-based incentive program with no upper limit on potential earnings.<br /></p><p>Weekly commission for the roadshow from $44 up to No Cap (Average $100 - $500).</p><p>This is an additional commission stream specifically tied to participation in roadshows.<br /></p><p>We provide significant performance-based incentives, allowing for potentially higher earnings beyond the basic salary.</p>",
